(72, 'Дунд шатыг дуусгах', 'Intermediate Wrap Up', '', 9, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You continue to amaze me.  You just blew through this intermediate course as if you\'ve done it before!  Lets see if you\'ve got what it takes to do the Advanced Course! (Though we both know you\'ll do great!)<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You continue to amaze me.  You just blew through this intermediate course as if you\'ve done it before!  Lets see if you\'ve got what it takes to do the Advanced Course! (Though we both know you\'ll do great!)<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 9),
(73, 'Гарыг хэсэгчилэх', 'Keyboard Quadrants', '', 1, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Wow, you are an ace.  Congratulations, that was some pretty difficult typing there.<\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">I would pat you on the back myself, but my lawyers tell me I can\'t.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Wow, you are an ace.  Congratulations, that was some pretty difficult typing there.<\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">I would pat you on the back myself, but my lawyers tell me I can\'t.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 10),
(74, 'Ур чадвар Зохиогч Дасгалууд', 'Skill Builder Drills', '', 2, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You have completed this lesson.  That is a most remarkable feat. You should sit back for a while and contemplate the meaning of life.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You have completed this lesson.  That is a most remarkable feat. You should sit back for a while and contemplate the meaning of life.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 10),
(75, 'Тэмдэг, Нарийвчилсан Цэг таслал', 'Symbols and Advanced Punctuation', '', 3, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You, my friend, are; amazing, awesome, fast.  Keep up the great work!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You, my friend, are; amazing, awesome, fast.  Keep up the great work!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 10),
(76, 'Нямбай дасгалууд', 'Accuracy Drills', '', 4, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first.When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first. When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Well, another lesson finished (assuming you have finished others, of course).  Here are some fun facts as a reward:<ul>  <li>35 MPH is the average speed most cars travel on interstate highways during peak morning and afternoon rush.<\\/li>  <li>The typical American family has 2-3 cars that each log in 15,000 miles per year.<\\/li>  <li>Root Beer was originally called Root Tea, however the name was changed to Root Beer to get more people to take interest in it.<\\/li>  <li>After 43 years of losing, Charlie Brown actually won a baseball game on March 30, 1993.<\\/li><\\/ul><\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Well, another lesson finished (assuming you have finished others, of course).  Here are some fun facts as a reward:<ul>  <li>35 MPH is the average speed most cars travel on interstate highways during peak morning and afternoon rush.<\\/li>  <li>The typical American family has 2-3 cars that each log in 15,000 miles per year.<\\/li>  <li>Root Beer was originally called Root Tea, however the name was changed to Root Beer to get more people to take interest in it.<\\/li>  <li>After 43 years of losing, Charlie Brown actually won a baseball game on March 30, 1993.<\\/li><\\/ul><\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 10),
(77, 'Цифр Товчлуур', 'The Numeric Keypad', '', 5, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You could be a typing Jedi Master :-)  One who types lots of numbers all day long..  a Number Typing Jedi Master.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You could be a typing Jedi Master :-)  One who types lots of numbers all day long..  a Number Typing Jedi Master.<\\/p>', 'Keypad', 10),
(78, 'Гүнзгий шатыг дуусгах', 'Advanced Wrap Up', '', 6, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">And another one bites the dust.  Excellent job, as always!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">And another one bites the dust.  Excellent job, as always!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 10),
