(318, 'Доод Мөрны Товчнууд', 'The Bottom Keys', 'BOTTOM_ROW', 3, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Одоо та Үндсэн Мөр ба Дээд Мөрийн товчнуудыг тухай мэдэж авсан тул бид Доод Мөр рүү шилжих болно. Бид долоотор хуруугаар <strong><key>V</key> ба <key>M</key> товч</strong>луур дарж эхэлнэ. </p><br /><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/v_m.png\" alt=\"Доод эгнээний хурууны байршил\" /></center>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you are feeling comfortable with the Home Row and Top Row keys, we will move to the Bottom Row.  We will start out with the index fingers reaching down to <strong>the <key>V</key> and <key>M</key> keys</strong>.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/v_m.png\" alt=\"Bottom Row Finger Position\" /></center>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You have completed the Bottom Row lesson.  If you are moving contiguously through the lessons, then you may still feel a bit shaky on each of the rows, but that is fine.  The next lesson will begin with the Home Row and branch out slowly.  Hey, these are beginner lessons after all!  <\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You\'re doing great.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You have completed the Bottom Row lesson.  If you are moving contiguously through the lessons, then you may still feel a bit shaky on each of the rows, but that is fine.  The next lesson will begin with the Home Row and branch out slowly.  Hey, these are beginner lessons after all!  <\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You\'re doing great.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 1),
(319, 'Амархан Нүүр Мөрны үгс', 'Easy Home Row Words', 'HOME_ROW_WORDS', 6, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Одоо та хуруугаа зөв байрлуулж, аль хуруугаа аль товчлуурыг цохиж, Бид Үндсэн Мөр дээрхээс эхэлдэг үгсийг бичихэд хялбар болж өөрчлөгдсөн тул амжилтанд хүрэх болно.</p><p><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/all_keys.png\" alt=\"Гарны Хурууны Байрлал\" /></center><br /></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Үсэг бичсэнийхээ дараа үндсэн мөрд таны хуруу буцахыг үргэлж санаж байх. Хэрвээ та аль хуруугаараа товч дарах ёстой гэдэгт эргэлзэж байвал дэлгэц дээрх гар ба гаруудаа лавлаж хараарай. Аль болох та гараасаа нүдээ салгахыг оролдоорой. Амжилт хүсье!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve got a hold on proper finger placement and which fingers hit which keys, we\\\'re going to kick it up a notch by moving into short, easy to type words that all start on the Home Row.</p><p><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/all_keys.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center><br /></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Always remember to return your finger to the home row after typing a letter.  Refer to the onscreen keyboard and hands if you are unsure as to which finger should press the key.  Try to keep your eyes off your hands as much as possible.  Good luck!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You rock!  You are now on your way to typing words without looking at your keys! Keep up the great work, you\'re making awesome progress.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You rock!  You are now on your way to typing words without looking at your keys! Keep up the great work, you\'re making awesome progress.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 1),
(320, 'Амархан Дээд Мөрны үгс', 'Easy Top Row Words', 'TOP_ROW_WORDS', 7, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Rinse and repeat!  We\\\'re now going to move on to words whose first letter originates on the top row.  The words are mostly simple.. mostly!  You may occasionally run across a word that will trip you up, just to keep you on your toes!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Та үг бүр бичихийн өмнө таны хуруунууд үндсэн мөр дээр байгааг шалгаарай. Хэрвээ та аль хуруугаараа товч дарах ёстой гэдэгт эргэлзэж байвал дэлгэц дээрх гар ба гаруудаа лавлаж хараарай. Аль болох та гараасаа нүдээ салгахыг оролдоорой. Амжилт хүсье!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Rinse and repeat!  We\\\'re now going to move on to words whose first letter originates on the top row.  The words are mostly simple.. mostly!  You may occasionally run across a word that will trip you up, just to keep you on your toes!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Make sure your fingers are on the home row before you type each word.  Refer to the onscreen keyboard and hands if you are unsure as to which finger should press the key.  Try to keep your eyes off your hands as much as possible.  Good luck!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">That was amazing!  In the next lesson, we\'ll get into some pretty wacky words as we bust into the bottom row keys.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">That was amazing!  In the next lesson, we\'ll get into some pretty wacky words as we bust into the bottom row keys.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 1),
(321, 'Амархан Доод Мөрны үгс', 'Easy Bottom Row Words', 'BOTTOM_ROW_WORDS', 8, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Доод мөр! Бид одоо энхний үсэг нь доод мөр дээр байралдаг үгнүүд рүү шилжин орж байна. Эдгээр үгсүүд магадгүй жаахан ... хөгжилтэй!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Та үг бүр бичихийн өмнө таны хуруунууд үндсэн мөр дээр байгааг шалгаарай. Хэрвээ та аль хуруугаараа товч дарах ёстой гэдэгт эргэлзэж байвал дэлгэц дээрх гар ба гаруудаа лавлаж хараарай. Аль болох та гараасаа нүдээ салгахыг оролдоорой. Амжилт хүсье!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">And last but not least, the bottom row!  We\\\'re now going to move onto words whose first letter originates on the bottom row, then branches out.  These words may be a little... funky!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Make sure your fingers are on the home row before you type each word.  Refer to the onscreen keyboard and hands if you are unsure as to which finger should press the key.  Try to keep your eyes off your hands as much as possible.  Good luck!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Saaawwweeeeettt!!!  You\'re now ready for the beginner wrap up!  Go shake your hands out, drink a fruit smoothie, and get ready for a big\'n!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Saaawwweeeeettt!!!  You\'re now ready for the beginner wrap up!  Go shake your hands out, drink a fruit smoothie, and get ready for a big\'n!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 1),
(322, 'Том үсгээр хямралын сурах', 'Learn to Bust a Capital Letter', '', 3, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">It\\\'s time to <strong>shift</strong> things into gear.  This lesson is going to teach you to capitalize letters on your keyboard.  To make a letter uppercase, hold down the SHIFT key while pressing the letter key.  It\\\'s that simple!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">The tip of the day is to shift with the hand opposite of the hand that is typing the uppercase letter.  So if you type an uppercase <key>F</key>, you should use your right hand shift.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/shift_keys.png\" alt=\"Home row Finger Position\" /></center>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">It\\\'s time to <strong>shift</strong> things into gear.  This lesson is going to teach you to capitalize letters on your keyboard.  To make a letter uppercase, hold down the SHIFT key while pressing the letter key.  It\\\'s that simple!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">The tip of the day is to shift with the hand opposite of the hand that is typing the uppercase letter.  So if you type an uppercase <key>F</key>, you should use your right hand shift.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/shift_keys.png\" alt=\"Home row Finger Position\" /></center>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Well then, that was fun!  The next lesson we\'re going to move into typing words that start with a capital letter.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Well then, that was fun!  The next lesson we\'re going to move into typing words that start with a capital letter.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(323, 'Том үгийн хямралыг сурах', 'Learn to Bust a Capital Word', '', 4, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve got a feel for shifting individual letters, lets move into typing words that start with a capital letter.  You may find this lesson challenging, but always remember proper form, keeping your hands on the home row, and to shift with the opposite hand.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">While typing this lesson, do your best to keep your eyes on the screen and off of your hands.  If you can\\\'t remember where a key is, use the onscreen keyboard and hands to help you type it.  Your key to typing fast is remembering where the keys are without looking!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve got a feel for shifting individual letters, lets move into typing words that start with a capital letter.  You may find this lesson challenging, but always remember proper form, keeping your hands on the home row, and to shift with the opposite hand.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">While typing this lesson, do your best to keep your eyes on the screen and off of your hands.  If you can\\\'t remember where a key is, use the onscreen keyboard and hands to help you type it.  Your key to typing fast is remembering where the keys are without looking!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">That was just amazing!  Now you can finally YELL AT PEOPLE OVER CHAT!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">That was just amazing!  Now you can finally YELL AT PEOPLE OVER CHAT!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(324, 'Эхлэгч шатыг дуусгах', 'Beginner Wrap Up', '', 9, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Тиймээ та энэ хүртэл хийж чадлаа. сайн ажиллаа! Энэ бол Дурд Курс руу шилжихийн өмнөх таны сүүлийн тест юм. Энэ хичээл нь таны энэ хүртэлэх сурсан, Үндсэн Мөрөөс эхлээд бүх зүйлээр сорих бөгөөд бүтэн өгүүлбэр рүү орно.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Гарнаасаа нүдээ салгахаа санаарай! Та мөгөдгүй спортын ундаа барж авахыг хүсэх байх учир нь энэ хичээл таныг хөлөрүүлэх болно.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">So you\\\'ve made it this far eh?  Great job!  This is your final test before moving on to the Intermediate Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\'ve learned so far, starting with the home row, and moving into full sentences!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! You may want to grab a sports drink because this lesson will make you sweat!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Wow, you just finished the entire Beginner Course!  That\'s just plain amazing.  Give yourself a pat on the back and get some rest before you start the Intermediate Course!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Wow, you just finished the entire Beginner Course!  That\'s just plain amazing.  Give yourself a pat on the back and get some rest before you start the Intermediate Course!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 1),
(325, 'Цагаан толгойн (A-M) сэргээх', 'Alphabet Soup (A-M)', '', 1, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"A\" and end at \"M\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"A\" and end at \"M\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">How do you feel?  Hope you don\'t feel like a beginner any more!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">How do you feel?  Hope you don\'t feel like a beginner any more!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(326, 'Цагаан толгойн (N-Z) сэргээх', 'Alphabet Soup (N-Z)', '', 2, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"N\" and end at \"Z\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"N\" and end at \"Z\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Awesome!  Keep up the great work and you\'ll be tweeting so fast you\'ll crash Twitter!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Awesome!  Keep up the great work and you\'ll be tweeting so fast you\'ll crash Twitter!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(327, 'Үндсэн Цэг Тэмдэглэл', 'Basic Punctuation', '', 5, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are now ready to move into basic punctuation.  This lesson will introduce you to punctuation that, depending on your keyboard format, does not require you to hit the shift key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">You will be doing a lot of typing with your right hand, so make sure to stretch it out first!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are now ready to move into basic punctuation.  This lesson will introduce you to punctuation that, depending on your keyboard format, does not require you to hit the shift key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">You will be doing a lot of typing with your right hand, so make sure to stretch it out first!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You, my friend, are; amazing, awesome, fast.  Keep up the great work!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You, my friend, are; amazing, awesome, fast.  Keep up the great work!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(328, 'Хамгийн нийтлэг үгс Англи хэл', 'Most Common English Words', '', 6, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This one should be fun.  This exercise is a run down of the 300 most used English words. These are words that you will be typing very often during your typing career.  It is recommended you practice this lesson many times!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Don\\\'t forget to keep your eyes off your keyboard!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This one should be fun.  This exercise is a run down of the 300 most used English words. These are words that you will be typing very often during your typing career.  It is recommended you practice this lesson many times!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Don\\\'t forget to keep your eyes off your keyboard!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">So that was confusing! I promise not to make more sense in the next lesson!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">So that was confusing! I promise not to make more sense in the next lesson!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(329, 'Хурд Үзүүлэх Сургалт', 'Speed Drills', '', 8, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Designed to help you improve your typing <strong>speed</strong>, this lesson will get you around the track in no time.</p><h4>Rules of the Game</h4><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson allows you a <span class=\"strong\">12% error margin</span>.  That\\\'s a lot, so this allows you to type quickly, and not worry about accuracy as much.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As always, we will be timing you.  From the time you type the first character until you hit the last letter, the timer will be going.  Try to use this to your advantage.  Watch your speed and try to beat that speed on the next exercise.  It\\\'s all about timing here!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you make too many mistakes, try again slower.  If you made no mistakes or only a few, try the next exercise faster.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Designed to help you improve your typing <strong>speed</strong>, this lesson will get you around the track in no time.</p><h4>Rules of the Game</h4><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson allows you a <span class=\"strong\">12% error margin</span>.  That\\\'s a lot, so this allows you to type quickly, and not worry about accuracy as much.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As always, we will be timing you.  From the time you type the first character until you hit the last letter, the timer will be going.  Try to use this to your advantage.  Watch your speed and try to beat that speed on the next exercise.  It\\\'s all about timing here!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you make too many mistakes, try again slower.  If you made no mistakes or only a few, try the next exercise faster.</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Here he comes, here comes Speed Racer!<\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You should be proud.  Your speed is increasing.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Here he comes, here comes Speed Racer!<\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You should be proud.  Your speed is increasing.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(330, 'Тооллого Захидал Тоо', 'Numbers Letters Numbers', '', 7, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Moving on up above the home row, you are going to learn how to hit the number keys.  Always remember to return your finger to its proper home row position after typing a letter or number. The numbers are broken up by finger allowing you to always practice proper finger movement.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you forget which finger should hit which key, refer to the onscreen keyboard and hand diagrams.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Moving on up above the home row, you are going to learn how to hit the number keys.  Always remember to return your finger to its proper home row position after typing a letter or number. The numbers are broken up by finger allowing you to always practice proper finger movement.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you forget which finger should hit which key, refer to the onscreen keyboard and hand diagrams.</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">y0u r0ck!  k33p 1t up!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">y0u r0ck!  k33p 1t up!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(331, 'Дунд шатыг дуусгах', 'Intermediate Wrap Up', '', 9, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You continue to amaze me.  You just blew through this intermediate course as if you\'ve done it before!  Lets see if you\'ve got what it takes to do the Advanced Course! (Though we both know you\'ll do great!)<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You continue to amaze me.  You just blew through this intermediate course as if you\'ve done it before!  Lets see if you\'ve got what it takes to do the Advanced Course! (Though we both know you\'ll do great!)<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 2),
(332, 'Гарыг хэсэгчилэх', 'Keyboard Quadrants', '', 1, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Wow, you are an ace.  Congratulations, that was some pretty difficult typing there.<\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">I would pat you on the back myself, but my lawyers tell me I can\'t.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_1.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Wow, you are an ace.  Congratulations, that was some pretty difficult typing there.<\\/p><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">I would pat you on the back myself, but my lawyers tell me I can\'t.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 3),
(333, 'Ур чадвар Зохиогч Дасгалууд', 'Skill Builder Drills', '', 2, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You have completed this lesson.  That is a most remarkable feat. You should sit back for a while and contemplate the meaning of life.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_2.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You have completed this lesson.  That is a most remarkable feat. You should sit back for a while and contemplate the meaning of life.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 3),
(334, 'Тэмдэг, Нарийвчилсан Цэг таслал', 'Symbols and Advanced Punctuation', '', 3, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You, my friend, are; amazing, awesome, fast.  Keep up the great work!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You, my friend, are; amazing, awesome, fast.  Keep up the great work!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 3),
(335, 'Нямбай дасгалууд', 'Accuracy Drills', '', 4, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first.When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first.When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Well, another lesson finished (assuming you have finished others, of course).  Here are some fun facts as a reward:<ul>  <li>35 MPH is the average speed most cars travel on interstate highways during peak morning and afternoon rush.<\\/li>  <li>The typical American family has 2-3 cars that each log in 15,000 miles per year.<\\/li>  <li>Root Beer was originally called Root Tea, however the name was changed to Root Beer to get more people to take interest in it.<\\/li>  <li>After 43 years of losing, Charlie Brown actually won a baseball game on March 30, 1993.<\\/li><\\/ul><\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">Well, another lesson finished (assuming you have finished others, of course).  Here are some fun facts as a reward:<ul>  <li>35 MPH is the average speed most cars travel on interstate highways during peak morning and afternoon rush.<\\/li>  <li>The typical American family has 2-3 cars that each log in 15,000 miles per year.<\\/li>  <li>Root Beer was originally called Root Tea, however the name was changed to Root Beer to get more people to take interest in it.<\\/li>  <li>After 43 years of losing, Charlie Brown actually won a baseball game on March 30, 1993.<\\/li><\\/ul><\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 3),
(336, 'Цифр Товчлуур', 'The Numeric Keypad', '', 5, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You could be a typing Jedi Master :-)  One who types lots of numbers all day long..  a Number Typing Jedi Master.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_3.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You could be a typing Jedi Master :-)  One who types lots of numbers all day long..  a Number Typing Jedi Master.<\\/p>', 'Keypad', 3),
(337, 'Гүнзгий шатыг дуусгах', 'Advanced Wrap Up', '', 6, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>', 0, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">And another one bites the dust.  Excellent job, as always!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">And another one bites the dust.  Excellent job, as always!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 3),
(338, 'Нүүр эгнээ ба гадна', 'Home row and Beyond', '', 4, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Үгсийн санд тавтай морилно уу! Энэ хичээлээр Үндсэн Мөр дээрээс олдсон үгсээр эхлээд <strong><key>I</key> ба <key>E</key> товчлууруудыг</strong> аажмаар оруулсан бүх энгийн үгсүүдийг бичхэд зааж өгөх болно.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Та яарах хэрэггүй, эхлэх бүртээ өөрийнхөөрөө хий, Үндсэн Мөр дээр бүх үгс байгаа. Хаана товч байгааг хайх гэж гар-руугаа бүү хар, булчингийнхаа ой санамжийг ашиглах зуршилтай болохын тулд дэлгэцэн дээрх компьютерийн гараас лавлана уу!</p><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/homerow_ie.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the world of words!  This lesson is going to teach you type very basic words starting with words found on the Home Row, and slowly introducing more letters, such as <strong>the <key>I</key> and <key>E</key> keys.</strong></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Take your time and do your best to always start and end each words on the home row.  Never look at your hands to find where a key is, always refer to the onscreen keyboard to get into the habit of using your muscle memory to type!</p><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/homerow_ie.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">That was great!  In the next lesson, we will venture out a bit further and practice some new fancy keys.<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">That was great!  In the next lesson, we will venture out a bit further and practice some new fancy keys.<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 1),
(340, 'Эрсдэлээс гарах', 'Venturing Out', '', 5, 0, 'LESSON', 1, '<p class=\"typinghelp\">Энэ бол гар дээрх үлдсэн товчнуудыг гаргаж ирэх цаг болжээ. Энэ хичээл нь доод эгнээнд төвлөрөх тул ердийнхөөс арай удаан бичиж байгааг анзаарч магадгүй юм.</p><p><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/all_keys.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center><br /></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Гар руу бүү хар учир нь үргэлж таны хуруунууд үсэг бүрийн дараа Үндсэн Мөр дээр буцаж байрладаг.</p>', '<p class=\"typinghelp\">It\\\'s time to venture out to the remaining keys on the keyboard.  This lesson will be very bottom-row-centric so you may notice yourself typing slower than normal.</p><p><center><img src=\"/typing/images/intros/all_keys.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center><br /></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Keep your eyes off your keyboard, and always place your fingers back on the homerow after each letter.</p>', 1, '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You\'re doing amazingly.  Keep up the good work and before you know it you\'ll be typing faster than your keyboard can handle!<\\/p>', '<img src=\\\"\\/tutor\\/images\\/congrats_4.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" align=\\\"left\\\" style=\\\"padding-right: 20px\\\" \\/><p class=\\\"typinghelp\\\">You\'re doing amazingly.  Keep up the good work and before you know it you\'ll be typing faster than your keyboard can handle!<\\/p>', 'Keyboard', 1),
